Miscellaneous Highlights: The Golden Jaguars will resume their debut League A campaign in the CONCACAF Nations League as they face-off against hosts Martinique at the Pierre-Aliker Municipal Stadium.
Others: Guyana had a forgettable debut as they lost their opening match 1-3 to Suriname at National Track and Field Centre in Leonora, with the contest being the team’s first local fixture in more than a year. It was also Guyana’s fifth defeat this year.
Martinique are in the identical position following a 1-3 loss away to Guatemala.
Guyana sealed their qualification to League A in the CONCACAF Nations League following a 5-0 record in Group D in League B.
